wsdl:operation.name: peopleMatchIDs
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve People IDs for probable matches for Name and Email entered.

wsdl:operation.name: peopleMatchIDsLooseFit
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve People IDs for probable matches for Name (begins with), City, State, ZIP and Email entered.

wsdl:operation.name: peopleIDsForAffiliation
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve People IDs in a comma-delimited string for people records with the specified affiliation code (a comma-delimited list of affiliation codes can be used).

wsdl:operation.name: peopleIDsForPhone
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve People IDs in a comma-delimited string for people records with the specified phone number (a comma-delimited list of phone number can be used).

wsdl:operation.name: peopleIDsForOrganization
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve People IDs in a comma-delimited string for people records with the specified organization name (wild cards can be used).

wsdl:operation.name: peopleIDsForCustomFieldID
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve People IDs in a comma-delimited string for people records with the specified custom field value (wild cards can be used and the custom field can be attached to either the people record or the address record).

wsdl:operation.name: addNameAndAddress
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Add a new name to IQ using a NameAndAddress object.

wsdl:operation.name: addName
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Add a new name to IQ . Set addressCheck=Y to perform address verification. Set homebus=H to indicate home address or B to indicate business address.

wsdl:operation.name: updateNameFields
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Update the name fields for an existing people record as identified by the peopleID #. Note that for any parameters left blank any existing value in the database will be deleted, except for the comments parameter (the value entered in the comments parameter is added to any existing comments).

wsdl:operation.name: addAddress
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Add a new address to an existing person. Set addressCheck=Y to perform address verification. Set homebus=H to indicate home address or B to indicate business address.

wsdl:operation.name: addAddressObj
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Add a new address to an existing person using an IQ address object. Set addressCheck=Y to perform address verification.

wsdl:operation.name: deleteAddressByID
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Deletes an existing address for a person. The address ID is required.

wsdl:operation.name: deleteAttachedObjectByID
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Deletes an existing attached file for a person. The object ID is required.

wsdl:operation.name: updateAddress
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Update an existing address record for which the address ID# is supplied. Set addressCheck=Y to perform address verification. Set homebus=H to indicate home address or B to indicate business address.

wsdl:operation.name: updatePreferredAddress
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Updates the existing preferred address for the person who's people ID# is supplied. Set addressCheck=Y to perform address verification. Set homebus=H to indicate home address or B to indicate business address.

wsdl:operation.name: updateAddressObj
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Post an address object to the address table. For use with existing address record only. AddressCheck=Y to re-standardize the address.

wsdl:operation.name: namesAndAddresses
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve names and address for the comma-delimited list of people IDs.

wsdl:operation.name: nameAndAddress
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve name and address information using the requested people ID #.

wsdl:operation.name: parseName
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Convert full name string to name and address object.

wsdl:operation.name: getPeopleID
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve a People ID by its E-Mail Address, Name, Address, etc.

wsdl:operation.name: getPeopleID_USING_FL_DOB_ID
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieves a Contact ID using the provided Last Name, First Name, Date of Birth, and/or Unique ID. If no existing contact record is found using those values, then a new contact record will be created using the additional information provided in the other fields unless ONLY_SEARH=true (if 'true' a search will be performed but a new record will NOT be created if there are no existing matches').

wsdl:operation.name: affiliationsForPeopleID

wsdl:operation.name: deleteCustomPeopleData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Delete custom people field information. The contact ID and custom field ID are required.

wsdl:operation.name: deleteCustomAddressData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Delete custom field information for an address. The address ID and custom field ID are required.

wsdl:operation.name: deleteCommunicationByID

wsdl:operation.name: nameAndAddress
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve name and address information using the requested people ID #.

wsdl:operation.name: parseName
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Convert full name string to name and address object.

wsdl:operation.name: getPeopleID
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve a People ID by its E-Mail Address, Name, Address, etc.

wsdl:operation.name: getPeopleID_USING_FL_DOB_ID
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieves a Contact ID using the provided Last Name, First Name, Date of Birth, and/or Unique ID. If no existing contact record is found using those values, then a new contact record will be created using the additional information provided in the other fields unless ONLY_SEARH=true (if 'true' a search will be performed but a new record will NOT be created if there are no existing matches').

wsdl:operation.name: affiliationsForPeopleID
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve list of active affiliations for a People ID as object array.

wsdl:operation.name: affiliations
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve list of active affiliations as object array.

wsdl:operation.name: addCustomPeopleData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Add custom people field information, providing the people ID, custom field ID and the data.

wsdl:operation.name: addCustomAddressData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Add custom address field information, providing people ID, address ID, the custom field ID and the data. If the address ID is left blank, the data will be added to the preferred primary address for the person.

wsdl:operation.name: deleteCustomPeopleData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Delete custom people field information. The contact ID and custom field ID are required.

wsdl:operation.name: deleteCustomAddressData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Delete custom field information for an address. The address ID and custom field ID are required.

wsdl:operation.name: addCommData
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Add communication info (e.g. phone number or email address) to a Person, providing the communication type and data. Set primary=Y if the record is to marked as the primary for the indicated comm type.

wsdl:operation.name: deleteCommunicationByID
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Deletes an existing communication record (phone number or email address) for a person. The communication ID is required.

wsdl:operation.name: addAffiliationCodes
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Add Affiliation Codes to a Person, providing a comma-delimited string of affiliationCodes.

wsdl:operation.name: removeAffiliationCodes
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Deletes Affiliation Codes for People (provide a comma-delimited string of poeple IDs and affiliation codes.

wsdl:operation.name: getChangedPeople
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieves Contacts (as NameAndAddress objects with custom fields data and affiliations) Added or Updated from the Given Date

wsdl:operation.name: getAttachedFileList
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve a list of attachments for a person.

wsdl:operation.name: getNewEMailPeople
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve All New People with an E-Mail Address from a Given DateTime in MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM AM Format.

wsdl:operation.name: getNewEMailPeopleCount
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve a Count of All New People with an E-Mail Address from a Given DateTime in MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM AM Format.

wsdl:operation.name: getNewEMailPeopleIDs
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve the People IDs of All New People with an E-Mail Address from a Given DateTime in MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM AM Format.

wsdl:operation.name: getMailingLabel
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve a name and primary address by its People ID #. The default format is to have lines delimited with carriage returns but optional delimiters can be specified (with special types of CR (default), CRLF, TAB, XML, BR (for web)).

wsdl:operation.name: getPeopleByID
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve a Person (as a NameAndAddress object) by its People ID #. Custom field values and affiliations are populated (those do not get populated when using nameAndAddress() method)

wsdl:operation.name: getAttachedFileByID
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve an attached file for a Person by its Object ID #.

wsdl:operation.name: prefixes
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve list of active prefixes (does NOT include IQ prefix code).

wsdl:operation.name: prefixCodes
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve list of active prefix codes and their translations.

wsdl:operation.name: suffixes
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve list of active suffixes (does NOT include IQ suffix code).

wsdl:operation.name: suffixCodes
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve list of active suffix codes and their translations.

wsdl:operation.name: stateAbbreviations
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve list of active state abbreviations.

wsdl:operation.name: stateCodes
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve list of active state codes.

wsdl:operation.name: commTypes
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve list of active communication type translations (does NOT include IQ comm type code).

wsdl:operation.name: commTypeObjects
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve list of active communication types as object array.

wsdl:operation.name: setProfilePicture
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Set people image attachment as profile picture.

wsdl:operation.name: removeProfilePicture
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Remove people image attachment as profile picture.

wsdl:operation.name: updateAttachedFilewithProfile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Attach a file (in byte array format) to person (as identified by peopleID) and set record security based on the profile.

wsdl:operation.name: attachFilewithProfile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Attach a file (in byte array format) to person (as identified by peopleID) and set record security based on the profile.

wsdl:operation.name: attachFile
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Attach a file (in byte array format) to person (as identified by peopleID).

wsdl:operation.name: validateAddress
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Validate an address (line1 and ZIP code are required). A populated address object is returned by this method.

wsdl:operation.name: addressCheckerVersion
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Returns the Address Checker version and database date used in address validation.

wsdl:operation.name: getAddresses
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve all of the existing addresses for a person (as identified by the peopleID).

wsdl:operation.name: getPreferredAddress
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve the preferred address for a person (as identified by the peopleID).

wsdl:operation.name: getPreferredAddressID
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve the address ID# for the preferred address for a person (as identified by the peopleID).

wsdl:operation.name: getPrimaryAddresses
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve all of the existing primary addresses for a person (as identified by the peopleID).

wsdl:operation.name: saveEmailAddress
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Save the email address for a person (as identified by peopleID).

wsdl:operation.name: savePrimaryEmailAddress
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Save the primary email address for a person (as identified by peopleID).

wsdl:operation.name: savePhoneNumber
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Save phone numbers for a person (as identified by peopleID).

wsdl:operation.name: activityCounts
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve the number of mail, workflow and board membership records for a person (as identified by peopleID).

wsdl:operation.name: getDetailPeopleLog
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve Detail People Log.

wsdl:operation.name: activeIQUsers
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve list of active user IDs and names as object array.

wsdl:operation.name: currentIQUserID
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve IQ user ID for the currently logged in user.

wsdl:operation.name: customPeoplefields
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieves a list item collection of the custom people field names and IDs. Special types (e.g. buttons) are excluded unless inclSpecial=Y. A field's 'Restricted Use' setting will be applied.

wsdl:operation.name: customAddressfields
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieves a list item collection of the custom address field names and IDs. Special types (e.g. buttons) are excluded unless inclSpecial=Y.

wsdl:operation.name: dashboardClasses
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieves a list of the available IQ Dashboard class names.

wsdl:operation.name: IQUserSecuritySettings
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieves a list of the available access privileges for the current user.

wsdl:operation.name: getIQVersion
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve the version information for the current IQ account.

wsdl:operation.name: getIQUIPreference
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: Retrieve the ALERTUI user setting for the current IQ user.
